<paragraph blockId="12.[192,780,910,934]" box="[192,780,910,934]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,374,910,934]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<typeStatus box="[192,260,910,934]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1878" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1878" box="[382,777,910,934]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Antigonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incisus">
<emphasis box="[382,599,910,933]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Antigonus incisus</emphasis>
Mabille, 1878
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[192,1440,958,1270]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,958,982]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Definition.</emphasis>
A genus without close relatives. Formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman and Salvin, [1896]" authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1896" box="[970,1434,958,982]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Staphylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[970,1095,958,982]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Staphylus</emphasis>
Godman and Salvin, [1896]
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1878" box="[192,279,990,1013]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Antigonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incisus">
<emphasis box="[192,279,990,1013]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">incisus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not monophyletic with the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1896" box="[646,772,990,1014]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Staphylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[646,772,990,1014]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Staphylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[779,833,990,1014]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Staudinger, 1876" authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1876" box="[936,1386,990,1014]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Helias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ascalaphus">
<emphasis box="[936,1163,990,1014]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Helias ascalaphus</emphasis>
Staudinger, 1876
</taxonomicName>
, nor with 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman and Salvin, [1896]" authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1896" box="[258,809,1022,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Scantilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opites">
<emphasis box="[258,452,1022,1046]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Scantilla opites</emphasis>
Godman and Salvin, [1896]
</taxonomicName>
(a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Plotz, 1886" authorityName="Plotz" authorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Tagiades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vincula">
<emphasis box="[1225,1439,1022,1046]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Tagiades vincula</emphasis>
Pl√∂tz, 1886
</taxonomicName>
) the 
<typeStatus box="[394,448,1054,1078]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman and Salvin, [1896]" authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1896" box="[580,1042,1054,1078]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Scantilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[580,694,1054,1078]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Scantilla</emphasis>
Godman and Salvin, [1896]
</taxonomicName>
, a genus-group name treated as a subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1896" box="[497,623,1086,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Staphylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[497,623,1086,1110]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Staphylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[640,715,1086,1110]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="11.[192,275,1906,1928]" captionTargetBox="[193,1440,780,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[192,1440,779,1883]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 4. Genomic trees of Carcharodini. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677243/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Keys to E.32.35b in 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[988,1156,1086,1110]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans (1953)</bibRefCitation>
. Readily distinguished from its relatives by the wing shape: forewing inner margin concave, hindwing outer margin excavate; forewing with hyaline apical spots; 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2569665573" collectionCode="T" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" specimenCode="T843" specimenCount="1">
uncus long and narrow, pointed at the tip, without side processes, no defined gnathos, valva less than twice longer than wide, penis shorter that in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1896" box="[1217,1343,1182,1206]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Staphylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1217,1343,1182,1206]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Staphylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a spined cornutus. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly23605.8.3:C247 
<collectionCode box="[1417,1435,1214,1238]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">T</collectionCode>
, aly5294.23.1:A538C, aly9588.6.1: 
<specimenCode box="[600,663,1246,1270]" collectionCode="T" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">T843</specimenCode>
C, aly 
<date box="[731,838,1246,1270]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" value="1370-07-02">1370.7.2</date>
:A1760G, aly345.13.8:A62C
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[192,1420,1294,1319]" box="[192,1420,1294,1319]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,1294,1318]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name, a masculine noun in the nominative singular, echoes the 
<typeStatus box="[1190,1243,1295,1319]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
species name.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[192,1439,1342,1398]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,433,1342,1366]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[498,551,1343,1367]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hayward, 1933" authorityName="Hayward" authorityYear="1933" box="[662,1101,1342,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Staphylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis box="[662,904,1342,1366]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Staphylus fasciatus</emphasis>
Hayward, 1933
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1872" box="[1165,1282,1342,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pholisora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1165,1282,1342,1366]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Pholisora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(?) 
<emphasis box="[1329,1439,1342,1366]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">angulata</emphasis>
Bell, 1937.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[192,787,1422,1446]" box="[192,787,1422,1446]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,380,1422,1446]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Verity, 1940" authorityName="Verity" authorityYear="1940" box="[460,783,1422,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Carcharodini">Carcharodini Verity, 1940</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[192,1439,1470,1526]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,344,1470,1494]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Comments.</emphasis>
Steinhauser doubted the placement of some of these species in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1896" box="[1130,1254,1470,1494]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Staphylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1130,1254,1470,1494]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Staphylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of morphological analysis (
<bibRefCitation author="Steinhauser" box="[488,707,1502,1526]" firstAuthor="Steinhauser" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 70" refId="ref28360" refString="Steinhauser, S. R. 1989. Taxonomic notes and descriptions of new taxa in the Neotropical Hesperiidae. Part I. Pyrginae. Bulletin of the Allyn Museum 127: 1 - 70." type="journal article" year="1989">Steinhauser 1989</bibRefCitation>
), and he was correct.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
